A large cordon is in place in a road in Manchester with forensics and Tactical Aid Unit officers at the scene. Part of Topley Street in the Collyhurst area of the city has been taped off. The cordon is in place near the corner with Rochdale Road.   Pictures from the scene show a shattered glass window with a small hole in the top right hand corner. Others show scores of officers scouring the scene for clues. Greater Manchester Police has been approached for comment. More to follow... We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. Please check back regularly for updates on this developing story . Get email updates on the day’s biggest stories straight to your inbox by signing up for our newsletters . Get all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you by following Express every time you see our name. Follow Express on Google News. Follow Express on Apple News. Follow Express on Flipboard. You can follow us and sign up for Twitter alerts here @daily_express. Keep up-to-date with your must-see news, features, videos and pictures throughout the day by following us on Facebook at  